{"ts":"2026-06-26T20:17:49.470Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Reviewing Task Requirements**\n\nI've got a solid grasp of the page's structure now. I'm carefully reviewing the task requirements, specifically the catalog build. The target directory is `/build/sandbox`, with landing page changes disabled. My focus is on upgrading that sandbox directory. I think I have a plan!\n\n\n**Defining Demo Parameters**\n\nI'm now nailing down the specifics for these agent demos. I'm focusing on building a local catalog with static data, and the landing page stays untouched. The goal is to cover all suggested demo categories, with cards that showcase each demo's purpose, workflow, industry focus, and platform relevance. Frontend-preview status is important. I'm also planning the filters: industry, function, and agent type. Finally, I'm working on a detailed, static demo interface.\n\n\n**Planning Internal Design**\n\nI'm now diving into the internal design, moving beyond catalog construction. I've sketched out the Sandbox Page narrative and visual metaphors. I'm aiming for a secure \"Enclave Control Center\" feel. I'm focusing on the \"Simulate before deploying\" narrative and the dark, elegant aesthetic with glowing cybernetic elements and workflow visualizations. My design also covers the layout strategy. Linting and building are next.\n\n\n**Designing the Hero Section**\n\nMy focus is the hero section, crafting a premium introduction that clarifies the Secure Sandbox Environment's purpose. I'm prioritizing an expensive and clear initial impression. I'm also planning the interactive control center, including low-profile filters for Industry, Function, and Agent Type, alongside a catalog grid of agent demos. Each card will concisely highlight key metadata. The details panel will function as a live workspace preview, showing detailed workflows and architecture.\n\n\n**Refining Simulation Interaction**\n\nI'm now refining the simulation interaction within the design. I'm focusing on the \"Run Dry-Run Simulation\" feature, ensuring a premium, realistic presentation. I plan to incorporate a local mock telemetry stream, enhanced with precise millisecond timestamps and visually appealing status indicators, which will enrich the scrolling logs. I'm also planning tabbed details and rich hover micro-interactions. My plan will incorporate Platform context.\n\n\n**Finalizing Style and Structure**\n\nI'm now focusing on the visual style and structure for the demo. I'm exploring subtle, colored glows for agent type representation on the cards. The responsive grid is central, shifting from side-by-side to stacked on smaller screens, and high-contrast, mobile-friendly filters will overflow horizontally. The `/app/build/sandbox/page.tsx` file is where I'll be making changes, and I'll avoid the landing page files and router logic. The aim is a design that is aligned with GFF AI's style, incorporating dark backgrounds, rich accents, high font contrast, and clean lines.\n\n\n**Detailing Agent Demos**\n\nI'm now detailing the first agent demo: Knowledge Search. It's a \"deep-reasoning\" agent for enterprise archives and telemetry. It will retrieve and synthesize data based on natural language queries, starting with an example thermal fatigue analysis. The agent uses GFF Embedder-v4 for semantic search, cross-references Oremesh data, and generates a failure mitigation report. My plans include a simulation log with timestamps and status updates.\n\n\n**Developing Agent Demos**\n\nI'm now detailing another agent demo, Procurement Copilot, designed for Retail and Supply Chain. It automates requisition validation and ERP updates. I'm focusing on the trigger which is triggered by an unmatched invoice, extraction details through the vision API, reconciliation with contracts, and variance flagging. I've designed simulation logs with timestamps and status updates.\n\n\n\n**Expanding Agent Demos**\n\nI'm now detailing another agent demo: Procurement Copilot, designed for Retail and Supply Chain. I'm focusing on the trigger which is triggered by an unmatched invoice, extraction details through the vision API, reconciliation with contracts, and variance flagging. I've designed simulation logs with timestamps and status updates. Now I'm working on the HR Assistant demo, which starts from an offer letter, triggering background checks and provisioning credentials. The plan is to visualize workflows, including an unmatched invoice example.\n\n\n**Defining New Simulation Events**\n\nI'm now detailing an HR Assistant workflow within the sandbox, specifically for candidate ID 88402. I've designed simulation events: credential generation in Microsoft Entra ID at 00:02, secure workspace setup at 00:03, customized onboarding at 00:04, and email notification at 00:05. I've also drafted the details for a \"Contract Intelligence\" demo, focusing on extraction of liabilities from uploaded agreements, with specific steps and triggers.\n\n\n\n**Constructing Simulation Scenarios**\n\nI'm now focusing on a new simulation: an Executive Dashboard. I'm building it for the Financial Services industry, using a Multi-Agent Synthesis agent on the Control Center platform. It will run daily at 06:00 UTC, with the goal of synthesizing operational data into briefings. Key steps will include performance metric aggregation and anomaly detection on treasury balances. I'm also planning the simulation logs, like the \"Contract Intelligence\" demo, focusing on the visual output.\n\n\n**Defining Simulation Steps**\n\nI'm now detailing a new simulation: an Executive Briefing Dashboard. This is for the Financial Services industry, using a Multi-Agent Synthesis agent on the Control Center platform. It will run daily at 06:00 UTC, with logs including querying 14 production platforms, synthesizing financial metrics, and structuring a briefing with Key Performance Indicators (KPIs). The simulation will also include a Compliance Assistant with \"continuous sovereign auditing\" and a schema change trigger.\n\n\n**Developing Agent Simulations**\n\nI'm now detailing a Customer Experience Agent, focused on Telecom. It focuses on high-empathy, context-aware user support within zero-trust limits. The simulation is a chat about international roaming bills. Steps include secure asset retrieval and diagnosis of bill shock from data roaming in Switzerland. The preview status is \"Ready for Simulation\". I've planned the workflow simulation, including billing data analysis, and ticket dispatch for compliance.\n\n\n**Planning New Simulation**\n\nI'm now detailing another simulation, this time an Operations Copilot. This agent focuses on real-time industrial sensor telemetry, predicting maintenance needs. I'm focusing on \"Heavy Industry & Mining\" and the related \"OreMesh\" platform. The workflow begins with a vibration threshold trigger, followed by fetching vibration charts and thermal scans. My plan is for \"Enclave Verified\" preview status.\n\n\n**Refining Operations Simulation**\n\nI'm now detailing an Operations Copilot simulation using the predictive maintenance model, including the specific steps. It will involve time-to-failure estimation and parts request generation, all within the SAP system. I'm focusing on the simulation logs which will include an ingestion of the IoT telemetry feed, FFT analysis, predictive health analysis, and the creation of a maintenance ticket. The estimated time to failure will be included in the logs.\n\n\n"}}
