he Data Ingress Source, which varies per agent, such as \"Audit logs\" or \"PDF files.\" The center has an enclave container with three connected sub-nodes. Finally, on the right, an interactive circle shows the Sovereign Target/Action.\n\n\n**Refining Simulation Interaction**\n\nI'm now iterating on the \"Launch Simulated Sandbox\" interaction. I've defined how the simulation should progress, focusing on a visually engaging and informative experience, including progress indicators, animated status updates, and telemetry logging. The design is completely frontend-only and adheres to all sandbox guidelines. I'm finalizing the logic for reset and agent selection. Now I'm ready to write the code.\n\n\n**Verifying Styling Details**\n\nI'm now focusing on specific styling for `page.tsx`. I'm verifying background colors, including deep backgrounds and accent colors like blue, red, green, and purple. I'm also considering high-quality typography with clean headers and monospace labels. I'll utilize Framer Motion transitions for dynamic elements. Plus, I will double-check the filters and I've reviewed the industries, functions, and agent types for implementation.\n\n\n"}}
